All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class PropagatedException
extends ViewDirectException

This exception is thrown when another exception occurs that the class cannot throw.

One such example might be a ICommand.execute function that experienced an IO error. Since the Execute function is not defined to throw IO Exceptions, you can issue a PropagatedException instead, as follows: 

 public void Execute() throws ViewDirectException {
    try {
       do something ....
    } catch (IOException e) {
       // uh oh, can't throw this exception in the execute
       // throw the PropagatedException instead. He can be thrown.
       throw new PropagatedException(e) ;
    }
 }
